      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        A parent searching for piano lessons for their 8-year-old is choosing an ongoing relationship, not just a service. They want to know: Is the teacher patient? Do kids enjoy it? Do students actually improve? Testimonials from current students and parents answer exactly those questions.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why music teaching testimonials are uniquely powerful</h2>
      <p>Music lessons are intensely personal. Your teaching style, personality, and approach matter as much as your credentials. A parent reading "my daughter used to dread practice, now she plays for an hour without being asked" is learning something about you that a resume never could. Authentic student testimonials are the most accurate preview of the experience you deliver.</p>

